    <div class="col-md-12">
        <p> Unfortunately, the cell phone reception here wasn't very good, probably due to the aluminum roof of the treehouse. But I wanted to have good reception when Steffi arrives in Manila. I found a tricycle to take me to the city, where I first went to a supermarket to really cool down. Steffi then reported that she had a good flight and everything is going smoothly. She's staying in Manila tonight and tomorrow at noon she'll finally fly into my arms here in Dumaguete. </p>
        <p> I then made myself comfortable with a donut and a much too sweet strawberry shake (today is officially sin day) before heading back to the accommodation. </p>
        <p> There, there was continuous noise from two directions until 9 p.m. Loud music was coming from speakers at the shopping mall across the street. Live music (pop and rock) was coming from a church behind the house. Since sleeping was out of the question, I decided to work a bit and block out the background noise with my good headphones. </p>
        <p> Tomorrow I'll have my little one all to myself again. I'm looking forward to it. </p>
